# Ball Knowledge — environment variables
#
# Real-time 1v1 multiplayer is OPTIONAL. The game is fully playable in
# local demo mode (vs a CPU) without any backend.
#
# To enable cross-device multiplayer, configure ONE of the providers below,
# then copy this file to ".env" (or ".env.local"). If both are set, Ably wins.

# --- Option A: Ably (recommended — no database, no server to deploy) ---
# Create a free app at https://ably.com and copy its API key.
# See ABLY_SETUP.md.
VITE_ABLY_API_KEY=

# --- Option B: Supabase (Realtime broadcast; reuses any existing project) ---
# See SUPABASE_SETUP.md. No SQL/tables required for live play.
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# --- OPTIONAL: Sign-in + cross-device progress sync (Firebase) ---
# Entirely optional and separate from multiplayer. When these are set, a
# "Sign in" button appears so players can save their Career, stats and daily
# streak to the cloud (passwordless email link + Firestore). All values are
# public client config. See FIREBASE_SETUP.md.
VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=
# Optional extras (not required for auth + Firestore):
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=
